Package: xhdfe
Type: Package
Title: Linear Regression with Multiple High-Dimensional Fixed Effects via a C++ Backend
Version: 2.20.0.20260723
Authors@R: c(
    person("Miguel", "Portela", email = "miguel.portela@eeg.uminho.pt", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Tiago", "Tavares", email = "tgstavares@eeg.uminho.pt", role = "aut"))
Description: Estimates linear models with multiple high-dimensional fixed
    effects using the xhdfe C++ backend -- the same compiled estimator behind
    the Stata 'xhdfe' command and the Python 'xhdfe' package. Supports multiway
    fixed effects, heterogeneous (group-specific) slopes, instrumental
    variables (2SLS), analytic and frequency weights, robust and multiway
    clustered standard errors, 'reghdfe'-style singleton dropping and
    degrees-of-freedom adjustments, 'fixest'-style small-sample corrections,
    fixed-effect recovery, group-level outcomes with individual fixed effects,
    and an optional CUDA GPU absorber. CPU behavior is the reference; results
    mirror 'reghdfe' (Correia, 2016) at the same nominal tolerance under the
    default 'reghdfe-comparable' tolerance mode.
